                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-02T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 2, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your circular telegram of February 1, 7 p.m. See the last paragraph of my
                    telegram No. 16 of January 28, 2 p.m.<note n="75" xml:id="d428fn75">It read: “At
                        Brazil’s request Paraguay today telegraphed Peru urging her to accept
                        Brazil’s proposal, already accepted by Colombia, to the effect that Peru
                        retire all Peruvians from Leticia after which Brazil will return the
                        territory to Colombia as a preliminary to a reconsideration of the treaty.”
                        (724.3415/2837)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
